64 bytes from del12s09-in-f14.1e100.net <span style="color: #3a81c3;">(</span>142.250.195.14<span style="color: #3a81c3;">)</span>: <span style="color: #715ab1;">icmp_seq</span>=8 <span style="color: #715ab1;">ttl</span>=118 <span style="color: #715ab1;">time</span>=58.4 ms

--- google.com ping statistics ---
8 packets transmitted, 8 received, 0% packet loss, time 7011ms
rtt min/avg/max/mdev = 58.377/79.799/146.107/30.594 ms
</pre>
</div>


<pre class="example">
$ping 192.168.1.11
PING 192.168.1.11 (192.168.1.11) 56(84) bytes of data.
Request timed out
Request timed out
Request timed out
</pre>
<p>
Here <b>Request time out</b>: Mean can't reach Server or Server is power down the 
Then error can be due to
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>firewall</li>
<li>network port issue,</li>
<li>broken cable,</li>
<li>bad connector,</li>
</ul>


<pre class="example">
#+begin_src 
$ping 192.168.1.11
PING 192.168.1.11 (192.168.1.11) 56(84) bytes of data.
